  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities</p>\n<p>· Plan, execute, monitor and control project as per contractual, client and QEHS requirements.</p>\n<p>· Ensure smooth implementation of work progress so project can be completed on time, within budget and meet contractual &amp; safety standards.</p>\n<p>· Manage suppliers and sub-contractors to ensure compliance in terms of QEHS, schedule and cost.</p>\n<p>· Define clear roles &amp; responsibilities, and deliverable requirements of team members.</p>\n<p>· Monitor construction productivity and provide recommendations for improvement to works.</p>\n<p>· Preparation of site progress report and necessary documentation.</p>\n<p>· Ensure that all project documentation including emails exchanges are maintained properly</p>\n<p>· Report to management periodically on status of project in terms of QEHS, cost and schedule.</p>\n<p>· Any other duties assigned by management.</p>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<p>· Posses degree in civil engineering, construction management or equivalent and safety certificates like CSCPM.</p>\n<p>· At least 8 years experience as project manager in building project</p>\n<p>· Able to work independently and lead project team</p>\n<p>· Proficient in Microsoft Project</p>\n<p>· Certified QM/ Conquas Manager would have an added advantage</p>",
